net.hudup.core.data

Class SysConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.data.PropList
      • net.hudup.core.data.DataConfig
        • net.hudup.core.data.SysConfig
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, TextParsable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EvaluatorConfig, ExternalConfig, ServerConfig

    public abstract class SysConfig
extends DataConfig
    Note, a configuration represented by DataConfig class stores configuration properties. Each property is a pair of key and value. This class extends directly DataConfig class, which is considered as a system configuration. It is used for system or important case. As a convention, this class is called system configuration. Every system configuration stores an internal URI string referred by its internal variable uri. Such URI string points to where to save (store, write) system configuration.
    Version:
    10.0
    Author:
    Loc Nguyen
